Kim Jong Il Inspects Companies of KPA Unit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 21 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected companies of KPA Unit 297. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first leg of his inspection was the 1st company of the third battalion of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He dropped in at its service commanding room to acquaint himself with the company's performance of combat duty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed satisfaction over the fact that the servicepersons of the company have performed their guard duty with a high degree of revolutionary vigilance and in a responsible manner and the company has intensified the working class education, equipping all of them with the transparent working class consciousness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took warm care of the living of the servicepersons, looking round an education room, a bedroom, a mess hall, a wash-cum-bath house, a non-staple food store, a barn and other places of the company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the commanding officers and soldiers of the company for keeping their barracks neat and tidy and assiduously managing their economic life in perfect unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the commanding officers have a very important role to play in establishing revolutionary discipline in the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He met Jon Hye Yong, company commander who graduated from the Kang Pan Sok Revolutionary School, praised her for devotedly serving at the post for defending the homeland with ardent patriotism, like her father who laid down his life for the Party and the revolution, and told her to become a fine woman revolutionary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the company. The next leg of his inspection was the 1st company of the 2nd battalion of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After acquainting himself with the company's performance of duty, he learned about how the training is conducted there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Praising the company for having obtained the top mark in the review of the drill by paying primary attention to the training, he stressed that it is a sure guarantee for increasing the combat capability to undergo an effective training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After being informed of the supply service by the commanding officers of the company, he went round entertainment and cultural and supply service facilities to get familiar with the soldiers' living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is good for the soldiers of the company to conduct brisk diverse cultural activities by use of frontline musical instruments and other instruments, he noted, urging the company to become a model in art activities, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He appreciated the successes made by the servicepersons of the company, expressing satisfaction over the fact that they are leading a revolutionary and militant life after successfully sprucing up their revolutionary post. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that all of the servicepersons of the KPA are heroes whose life is shining like stars as they remain loyal to the Party, he added that the Korean revolution is making a steady advance as the era is steered by this group of revolutionaries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the company.

Chinese Senior Official on Sino-Korean Relations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beijing, November 20 (KCNA) -- Gu Xiulian, vice-chairperson of the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress, Monday met and had a friendly talk with the delegation of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries headed by its acting Chairman Mun Jae Chol on a visit to China at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gu Xiulian said that China and Korea are the friendly neighbors linked by a mountain and rivers and the Sino-Korean friendship provided by revolutionaries of the elder generation of the two countries is the one which stood all sorts of test of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the political trust and cooperative relations in various fields including economy and culture have grown stronger between China and the DPRK, Gu said that the mutual visits of the top leaders of the two countries in recent years marked an important occasion in putting the bilateral friendly relations on a new level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gu stressed that the Korean people have achieved many successes in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation overcoming difficulties under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Maltese Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 21 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, received credentials from Karl Xuereb, Maltese ambassador to the DPRK, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After receiving the credentials the president had a talk with the ambassador.

Greetings to Lebanese President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 21 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Wednesday sent a message of greetings to Lebanese President Emile Lahoud on the occasion of the 64th anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim in the message sincerely wished the national reconciliation and unity in Lebanon and the Lebanese people well-being.

Traditional Kimchi Pickling Begins in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 21 (KCNA) -- All the families of the DPRK have begun to make traditional Kimchi late in November. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kimchi pickling is rather behind time this year with the growing of vegetables for Kimchi seriously affected by the biggest flood ever seen. But it has never dampened the zeal of housewives to delight the members of their families with Kimchi as tasty as ever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Myong Ae, a researcher at the Foodstuff Research Institute under the State Academy of Sciences who had invented a new functional Kimchi told KCNA that the Korean women were showing greater zeal in preserving the peculiar taste of Kimchi, a national food. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They regard making Kimchi as a matter of developing the national food and keeping alive national character.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the pickling season every year housewives visit elders to learn the knack and experience they have attained through decades and apply new pickling methods to make Kimchi more delicious by folk ways. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Most families generally make not only whole cabbage Kimchi but also various other kinds such as red leaf mustard Kimchi, Kimchi wrapped in large cabbage leaves, hot pickling of chopped radish and radish pickled in salt water. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nowadays mass media are extensively introducing to housewives lactic acid bacilli powder, culture fluid of lactic acid bacilli, etc for retaining the peculiar taste of Kimchi and extending its preserving period.

Pyongyang Building Materials Factory Commissioned 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 21 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyang Building Materials Factory has been commissioned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The factory having all production processes furnished with up-to-date equipment is capable of producing tiles, sanitary ware, artificial marble, coating materials, plastic window frames and other quality materials to make a positive contribution to the development of the nation's building materials industry and the improvement of the standard of people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A commissioning ceremony took place on the spot on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Jon Sung Hun, vice-premier of the Cabinet, officials concerned and builders and employees of the factory.

First Snow Falls Heavily in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 21 (KCNA) -- The first snow fell heavily in the east and west coastal areas including Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Chol Su, vice-chief of the Central Meteorological Institute, told KCNA that the first snow had fallen lightly usually in the country but this year witnessed rather heavy snow in the light of the first snow precipitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said: It snowed 11 centimeters in Pyongyang from 18:00 to 24:00 and 12 centimeters in Sinuiju City from 12:00 to 20:00 on Nov. 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Heavy snow was also witnessed in Pukchang, Kusong, Sariwon, Haeju, and other parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, it was unusual that it snowed, accompanied with lightning flashes. 
 Snow also fell in many regions on the night of Nov. 20.

Japan Urged to Redress Its Past Crimes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 21 (KCNA) -- A resolution on the issue of "comfort women" for the Imperial Japanese Army introduced by the VVD of Netherlands was adopted at the Second Chamber with unanimous approval on Nov. 8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the European Parliament is pushing forward the move to adopt the similar resolution. It has already invited survivors of the sexual servitude for the Imperial Japanese Army to hear their testimonies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson today observes in a signed commentary carried in this regard: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said issue is now under serious discussion at the European Parliament in the wake of the passage of a resolution on the issue through the U.S. House of Representatives in July last. This development goes to prove that the issue of Japan's settlement of its war crimes is raised as a task of the times the fulfillment of which brooks no further delay and has become a unanimous desire of the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan, however, has worked hard to evade its responsibility for its war crimes at any cost, denying them though more than half a century has passed since its defeat in the war, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has become a worldwide trend in the new century for humankind to liquidate inglorious past and turn over a new leaf. It is only the Japanese reactionaries that make desperate efforts to keep Japan's past crimes buried into oblivion for good. This behavior clearly proves that they are a group of barbarians as they are bereft of even an iota of human conscience and quality. That is why Japan is isolated diplomatically, after becoming a target of derision and contempt of the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are, however, going so foolish as to talk about someone's "human rights abuse" in a bid to paint Japan as a victim. This behavior only provokes a sense of aversion among all people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's persistent efforts to evade the settlement of its past crimes would touch off stronger hatred and protest among the international community. And for this it will not escape a stern judgement of justice and human conscience.

Reckless Act of Security Authorities' Suppression of People's Just Actions Denounced in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 21 (KCNA) -- The "Organizing Committee for the Day of All-People's Action for 2007" in south Korea reportedly called a press conference on November 16 at which it denounced the security authorities for their brutal suppression of the all-people actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the press conference accused the security authorities of disallowing the all-people struggle expected to take place on Nov. 11, the day of all-people's action in 2007 for checking the conclusion of the south Korea-U.S. FTA, for the abolition of part-time jobs and for peace against war and mobilizing a huge police force to mercilessly crack down upon the struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Demanding the immediate resignation of the police agency chief who ordered the police to put down the all-people struggle by force, the press release declared that with nothing can they hold in check the above-said people's struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization would once again demonstrate the people's will and might through the struggle to be staged on December 1 on the occasion of the "second day of the all-people action," added the press release.

Kim Jong Il's Work Carried in Mexico
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 21 (KCNA) -- The Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism carried the detailed gist of Kim Jong Il's work "The Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy" in its information bulletin No. 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on July 26, Juche 85 (1996), makes a scientific analysis of the limitation of the time the preceding philosophy was enunciated and the originality of the Juche philosophy and clarifies the idea that the Juche philosophy serves as a revolutionary philosophy and political philosophy of the Workers' Party of Korea and the principled matters arising in studying and explaining the Juche philosophy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin carried a picture of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il standing together.

Gu Xiulian se refiere a relaciones de amistad entre Corea y China
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beijing, 20 de noviembre (ATCC) -- La vicepresidenta del Comite Permanente de la Asamblea Popular Nacional (APN) de China, Gu Xiulian, sostuvo el dia 19 en el Gran Palacio del Pueblo de Beijing amistosas conversaciones con la delegacion del Comite Coreano de Relaciones Culturales con el Extranjero presidida por su presidente interino, Mun Jae Chol, que realiza una visita a China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion, Gu Xiulian dijo que China y Corea son vecinos amistosos colindados con montanas y rios y subrayo que la amistad bilateral preparada por los revolucionarios de veterana generacion de los dos paises se sobrepuso a todas las pruebas de la historia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras referirse al fortalecimiento y desarrollo de la confianza politica y de las relaciones de colaboracion entre ambos paises en varias esferas como la economia y cultura, senalo que las visitas reciprocas realizadas en los ultimos anos por los maximos dirigentes de los dos paises marcaron un importante hito para situar en una nueva etapa las relaciones de amistad China-Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A continuacion, enfatizo que bajo la sabia guia del Dirigente Kim Jong Il, el pueblo coreano logra muchos exitos en la construccion de una gran potencia prospera socialista superando las dificultades.
